police station&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><span style=\"color:rgb(193, 168, 118)\">Phone number</span></strong><br />\r\n(965) 24759921 / 24759916<br />\r\nFax: 24759228</div>\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(210,'eng','DynamicPage',70,'short',''),(474,'eng','DynamicPage',158,'short',''),(255,'eng','DynamicPage',85,'short',''),(256,'eng','DynamicPage',86,'title','Lighting and smart home solutions'),(257,'eng','DynamicPage',86,'text','The Lighting &amp; Smart Solutions Division&rsquo;s mission is to provide customers with the best lighting &amp; smart building solutions. Its main objective is satisfying all customers &ndash; individuals, wholesalers and project representatives &ndash; by providing them with a hassle-free customer friendly shopping experience, accessible technical know-how, and &nbsp;a home automation &amp; lighting design.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nLighting Division is located in Shuwaikh &ldquo;Panasonic Showroom&rdquo;. There is a complete range of lighting fittings, fixtures, bulbs, wiring accessories, professional sound systems, home theaters &amp; home automation solutions.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Division offers leading brands from major suppliers in Europe, USA, Japan China, the Netherlands, Saudi Arabia, Spain, Taiwan, Thailand, and the UK. The products and services are economically priced for decoration, utility or security in residential, commercial, architectural, institutional and industrial applications.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWe ensure that only goods of high quality and value are made available. The Division provides one of the best after-sales technical support and services by having the&rdquo;first LED lighting technical service center with full range of LED lighting spare parts in Kuwait&rdquo;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/1.jpg\" style=\"height:285px; width:404px\" />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/2.jpg\" style=\"height:285px; width:401px\" /><br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(477,'eng','DynamicPage',159,'short',''),(336,'eng','DynamicPage',112,'short',''),(270,'eng','DynamicPage',90,'short',''),(271,'eng','DynamicPage',91,'title','Tours & Travel'),(272,'eng','DynamicPage',91,'text','<div><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Incorporated in 1994, </span>Al-Yousifi <span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Tours &amp; Travel has built an impeccable reputation for exceptional service in three specific travel markets: corporate, leisure, luxury. </span><br />\r\n<br />\r\nAl-Yousifi <span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Tours &amp; Travel built its reputation by providing superior service in the areas of corporate, leisure, luxury</span>.<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> we take pride in exceeding the expectations of our diverse client portfolio of Fortune 200 companies, local and international, along with thousands of individual travelers.</span></div>\r\n'),(328,'eng','DynamicPage',110,'title','Denon'),(329,'eng','DynamicPage',110,'text',''),(330,'eng','DynamicPage',110,'short',''),(331,'eng','DynamicPage',111,'title','Flame Gas'),(332,'eng','DynamicPage',111,'text',''),(333,'eng','DynamicPage',111,'short',''),(334,'eng','DynamicPage',112,'title','Ignis'),(335,'eng','DynamicPage',112,'text',''),(273,'eng','DynamicPage',91,'short',''),(274,'eng','DynamicPage',92,'title','Al Yousifi Watches Center'),(275,'eng','DynamicPage',92,'text','Al-Yousifi has been the authorized agent in Kuwait for Citizen Watches and clocks since 1975. Citizen brand watches are available in more than 500 distinct and unique models and are retailed in Kuwait at very competitive prices. Having complete customer satisfaction in mind, the division imports only the best of world class watches, and is the authorized distributor in Kuwait for Citizen, Swistar, Brosway, Triumph, Regnier, Tokyoflash, Chipie, Thierry Mugler, Fuel, Gallucci, Versay and Elysee.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAl-Yousifi Watches has many dedicated showrooms and a respected network of dealers. Well-equipped service centers have been set up to offer the growing clientele a satisfying after-sales experience.<br />\r\nTechnician training is done overseas at the suppliers&rsquo; repair centers. Al-Yousifi&rsquo;s focus on the needs of its customers ensures that Al-Yousifi Watches continues acquiring new brands of timepieces from all over the world.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(258,'eng','DynamicPage',86,'short',''),(259,'eng','DynamicPage',87,'title','Ocean Star '),(260,'eng','DynamicPage',87,'text','Ocean Star Establishment, a subsidiary of Easa Husain Al-Yousifi &amp; Sons, has distributed a wide variety of toys, gifts and consumer products in Kuwait since its inception in 1995.<br />\r\nOcean Star has its own offices, warehousing and distribution facilities and operates independently of other Al-Yousifi profit centers. However, Ocean Star enjoys a similar network of dealers as Al-Yousifi&rsquo;s electronics business.<br />\r\nIn 2009<span style=\"color:black\">,</span> Ocean Star was restructured to have the Musical Instruments and Arcade Divisions under its direct supervision. This restructuring process was triggered by Al-Yousifi&rsquo;s strategy to increase synergy among divisions while reducing operating costs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(261,'eng','DynamicPage',87,'short',''),(473,'eng','DynamicPage',158,'text','In the early 1970s, when Easa Husain Al-Yousifi realized the importance of music to the wellbeing of society and the development of the individual, he began selling traditional musical instruments and sponsoring local concerts. He also arranged for lessons in how to play the instruments he sold. Everything from grand pianos to microphone stands is sold at these showrooms<span style=\"color:black\">:</span> Kawai, Roland, Power Beat, General Music, and Ibanez<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:black\">G</span>uitars are a few of the top-quality brands available.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nContinuing the tradition of the founder, Easa Husain Al-Yousifi&amp; Sons is one of the foremost<br />\r\nSponsors of musical events in Kuwait. These include multi-instrument concerts and piano<br />\r\nRecitals in leading hotels and at major festivals.<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(472,'eng','DynamicPage',158,'title','Music'),(469,'eng','DynamicPage',157,'title','Toys'),(470,'eng','DynamicPage',157,'text','Sega, Konami, ICE, Skee-Ball, Smart Ice Arena,Moser, I.E. Park, Falgas, Inter card, Power Paddler and<br />\r\nRobogeddon are just a few of the well-known brands of entertainment equipment from the US, Canada,<br />\r\nEurope and Japan that Al-Yousifi represents in Kuwait. The Arcades Division was established in 1993 after an in-depth survey of the Kuwaiti market for amusements.<br />\r\nToday<span style=\"color:black\">,</span> the Division is the country&rsquo;s foremost distributor of coin-operated entertainment equipment. These amusements are mainly for children of two to fourteen years, a sizeable percentage of the local Population.<br />\r\nThe equipment is sold directly to affiliates of government-owned companies and to private sector<br />\r\nOperators of amusement facilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(268,'eng','DynamicPage',90,'title','Sweet Land Chocolate Factory Cocoa Leaf'),(269,'eng','DynamicPage',90,'text','In 2004, Al-Yousifi opened the first chocolate factory in Kuwait and called it Sweet Land. Production was set up to be handled and supervised by specialists in chocolate manufacturing.<br />\r\nToday, the Sweet Land factory sells its chocolate to other sweets and pastry businesses in the forms of blocks to be used as an ingredient in their production of sweets and desserts. Sweet Land not only supplies the local market with these chocolate blocks, but also exports to businesses in neighboring countries.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn addition, Sweet Land produces, packages, and sells ready-made chocolate singles in a variety of chocolate types, fillings and shapes. Customers wanting chocolate as gifts for special occasions may order according to individual specifications and may choose from among several exquisite styles of packaging.<br />\r\nSweet Land opened Cocoa Leaf, its first chocolate shop, in 2007 located in Salmiya can be seen from the gulf road.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp; <img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/cocoa-leaf-1(1).jpg\" style=\"height:132px; width:400px\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/cocoa-leaf-2.jpg\" style=\"height:134px; width:370px\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/0%20(3).jpg\" style=\"height:293px; width:400px\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/0%20(10).jpg\" style=\"height:294px; width:440px\" /><br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(325,'eng','DynamicPage',109,'title','DeLonghi'),(326,'eng','DynamicPage',109,'text',''),(327,'eng','DynamicPage',109,'short',''),(276,'eng','DynamicPage',92,'short',''),(277,'eng','DynamicPage',93,'title','Eassa Hussein Yousifi for Real Estate'),(278,'eng','DynamicPage',93,'text','Easa Husain Al-Yousifi&amp; Sons has been investing in real estate since its inception, when the founder bought the site on which his first showroom was built.<br />\r\nAs profit from the company&rsquo;s core business in consumer electronics mounted, some of the surplus was invested in real estate in Kuwait. Several sites were used to build apartments for rent, while other sites were held for resale in a rising market.<br />\r\nAl-Yousifi&rsquo; real estate portfolio consists of low- and high-rise buildings mostly in Kuwait and the UAE. The latest Al-Yousifi building to be constructed is the Panasonic Tower, named in honor of the long-lasting relationship between Al-Yousifi and Panasonic. It is located in the heart of Kuwait&rsquo;s business district.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/IMG_3922%20(24).jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:300px\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"/app/webroot/js/ckfinder/userfiles/images/Untitled-1.jpg\" style=\"height:450px; width:300px\" /><br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(279,'eng','DynamicPage',93,'short',''),(476,'eng','DynamicPage',159,'text','Gold can be crafted into beautiful ornaments for personal wear or it can be bought as an investment. It is in very high demand, both as jewelry and as financial security during currency crises. To serve this market, Al-Yousifi opened a gold shop in Kuwait City in 1991.<br />\r\nThe shop sells 21- and 22-carat gold jewelry, mainly in Arabic and Indian styles, and small bars of pure 24 carat gold in various sizes. This first shop was so successful that a second shop, specializing in diamond-encrusted jewelry, was opened in 1994 in Salmiya and a third shop was opened in 2001 in Kuwait City.<br />\r\nAll the precious metal jewelry sold in Al- Yousifi shops has a reputation for exquisite design and fine craftsmanship.<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(475,'eng','DynamicPage',159,'title','Easa Husain Al-Yousifi for jewelry '),(285,'eng','DynamicPage',95,'short',''),(286,'eng','DynamicPage',96,'title','Advanced'),(287,'eng','DynamicPage',96,'text',''),(288,'eng','DynamicPage',96,'short',''),(289,'eng','DynamicPage',97,'title','I-brands Dubai '),(290,'eng','DynamicPage',97,'text',''),(291,'eng','DynamicPage',97,'short',''),(462,'eng','DynamicPage',154,'short',''),(489,'eng','DynamicPage',163,'short','Easa Husain Al-Yousifi & Sons Co.  introduces the revolutionary IPL (Intense Pulsed Light) Machine from Panasonic in the Kuwaiti Market '),(490,'eng','DynamicPage',164,'title','Community Work'),(491,'eng','DynamicPage',164,'text','During his lifetime, Easa Husain Al-Yousifi was renowned for his charitable works. These have now been formalized and are overseen by Al-Yousifi&rsquo;s Public Relations Department The scope of these activities has been broadened and includes the sponsorship of social events, organized by both government authorities and private societies.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThese events are supported with funding or gifts of products. The company donates office supplies, electronics and computers to schools run by the Ministry of Education. Al-Yousifi is also a keen sponsor of public awareness campaigns on matters of social concern in Kuwait, such as electricity and water conservation, environmental pollution, and drug abuse.<br />\r\nAlso, the Al-Yousifi Charity fund plays a big role in charity support and sponsorship of many nonprofit organizations and humanitarian institutions, and recently the charity fund became the sponsor of the Real Madrid football Academy in Kuwait for children.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),(492,'eng','DynamicPage',164,'short','During his lifetime, Easa Husain Al-Yousifi was renowned for his charitable works. These have now been formalized and are overseen by Al-Yousifi’s Public Relations Department'),(493,'eng','DynamicPage',165,'title','Public Relations'),(494,'eng','DynamicPage',165,'text','<span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Al-Yousifi&rsquo; Public Relations Department creates, maintains and enhances the corporate identity and image. The Department also plays a key role in organizing and coordinating the advertising campaigns and special promotions for which Easa Husain Al- Yousifi &amp; Sons is justly famous. To enhance the image of the internationally-known brands it represents, the individual sales divisions within Al-Yousifi participate in trade exhibitions and similar publicity generating activities. These activities are organized and coordinated by Public Relations, which is noted for its ability to present grand openings that generate extensive publicity.</span>'),(495,'eng','DynamicPage',165,'short','Al-Yousifi’ Public Relations Department creates, maintains and enhances the corporate identity and image. ');
